From caf2b3a488d1084770408cbe1100baf92f5957fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sultech <6282-Sultech@users.noreply.gitlab.gnome.org>
Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 05:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 09/17] native: Fix ghost cursor by blocking cursor updates
 during tearing

The ghost cursor bug occurs because the Linux kernel rejects async (tearing)
commits that modify anything other than the primary plane's FB_ID. This is
documented in the kernel DRM documentation and enforced by the atomic modesetting
code.

When Mutter enables tearing and inhibits the hardware cursor, it tries to clear
the cursor sprite by calling meta_kms_cursor_manager_update_sprite(..., NULL).
However, this cursor plane update is incompatible with async page flips and
causes undefined behavior - the kernel may reject the update, partially apply it,
or leave a ghost cursor on screen.

KWin's Solution (from kwin-6.5.5):
KWin solves this by checking if non-primary planes (cursor) are enabled when
tearing is requested. If they are, KWin falls back to VSync instead of using
tearing. Their code comment states: "The kernel rejects async commits that
change anything but the primary plane FB_ID".

Mutter's Fix:
Instead of trying to clear the cursor sprite when tearing is enabled, we simply
block ALL cursor plane updates (including the clear operation) when the update
is async. This means:
1. Cursor plane keeps its existing state (doesn't change)
2. No ghost cursor appears because we never attempt the problematic clear
3. Software cursor rendering handles cursor display during tearing
4. When tearing is disabled, cursor updates resume normally

This matches the kernel's expectation that async commits only modify the primary
plane, and avoids the race condition entirely by never attempting the cursor
plane update in the first place.

Signed-off-by: Vasiliy Stelmachenok <ventureo@cachyos.org>
---
 src/backends/native/meta-kms-cursor-manager.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/backends/native/meta-kms-cursor-manager.c b/src/backends/native/meta-kms-cursor-manager.c
index caec41240c..aa7bc69a56 100644
--- a/src/backends/native/meta-kms-cursor-manager.c
+++ b/src/backends/native/meta-kms-cursor-manager.c
@@ -462,6 +462,21 @@ update_filter_cb (MetaKmsImpl       *impl,
   MetaThreadImpl *thread_impl = META_THREAD_IMPL (impl);
   MetaKmsCursorManagerImpl *cursor_manager_impl = user_data;
 
+  /* GHOST CURSOR FIX: The Linux kernel rejects async (tearing) commits that
+   * modify anything other than the primary plane's FB_ID. When tearing is
+   * enabled and we try to clear/update the cursor sprite, this causes
+   * undefined behavior including ghost cursors.
+   *
+   * Solution: Block ALL cursor plane updates when in async mode. The cursor
+   * plane keeps its last state, and software cursor rendering handles display.
+   * This matches KWin's approach and the kernel's documented behavior.
+   *
+   * Reference: KWin drm_output.cpp shouldDisableNonPrimaryPlanes() */
+  if (update && meta_kms_update_get_async (update))
+    {
+      return update;
+    }
+
   if (flags & META_KMS_UPDATE_FLAG_TEST_ONLY)
     return update;
 
-- 
