From 277b0977e30def9b4a6eacf629ad6260c287da0d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sultech <6282-Sultech@users.noreply.gitlab.gnome.org>
Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 06:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 12/17] Add backend cursor inhibit for smooth tearing
 transitions

Adds backend-level hardware cursor inhibit/uninhibit when entering/exiting
tearing mode. This works together with the KMS-level blocking to provide:
- Smooth transitions without cursor stuttering
- Clean switch between hardware and software cursor
- No visual glitches during mode changes

The two-level approach ensures both ghost cursor prevention (KMS level) and
smooth transitions (backend level).

Signed-off-by: Vasiliy Stelmachenok <ventureo@cachyos.org>
---
 src/backends/native/meta-onscreen-native.c | 12 +++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

